Parliament, Thursday, 28 May 2020 – The Joint Standing Committee on the Financial Management of Parliament will this afternoon, from 15:00 to 18:00, hold a virtual meeting to be briefed by the Acting Secretary to Parliament, Ms Baby Tyawa, on Parliament’s performance in the 4th quarter of 2019/20 financial year. The committee is composed of Members of the National Assembly and Members of the National Council of Provinces and it is co-chaired by Ms Peace Mabe and Ms Dikeledi Mahlangu.
	
	In addition, today marks the Sub-Committee of the Portfolio Committee on Communication’s third day of virtual interviews with the 20 shortlisted candidates to fill four Media Development and Diversity Agency (MDDA) Board vacancies. The interviews will start in the evening from 18:00 to 21:00, and the last round is scheduled to be completed tomorrow.
	
	Members of the media who would like to be part of the meetings to observe may forward their contact details to Mr Mlindi Mpindi on 081 716 7329 for inclusion in the Parliament Communications Service WhatsApp group, where login details will be shared.
	
	Members of the public may get involved and follow committee sittings live on Parliament TV (DStv Channel 408), via live stream on Parliament YouTube channel and Twitter page on the links below. You may subscribe to the Parliament YouTube channel to receive instant notification of live feeds.
	
	Twitter: https://twitter.com/ParliamentofRSA
	Facebook: https://facebook.com/ParliamentofRSA
	 YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/ParliamentofRSA
	
